445enum UnitFlags : uint32
446{
447 UNIT_FLAG_NONE = 0x00000000,
448 UNIT_FLAG_SERVER_CONTROLLED = 0x00000001, // set only when unit movement is controlled by server - by SPLINE/MONSTER_MOVE packets, together with UNIT_FLAG_STUNNED; only set to units controlled by client; client function CGUnit_C::IsClientControlled returns false when set for owner
449 UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE = 0x00000002, // not attackable
450 UNIT_FLAG_DISABLE_MOVE = 0x00000004,
451 UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED = 0x00000008, // controlled by player, use _IMMUNE_TO_PC instead of _IMMUNE_TO_NPC
452 UNIT_FLAG_RENAME = 0x00000010,
453 UNIT_FLAG_PREPARATION = 0x00000020, // don't take reagents for spells with SPELL_ATTR5_NO_REAGENT_COST_WITH_AURA
454 UNIT_FLAG_UNK_6 = 0x00000040,
455 UNIT_FLAG_NOT_ATTACKABLE_1 = 0x00000080, // ?? (UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED | UNIT_FLAG_NOT_ATTACKABLE_1) is NON_PVP_ATTACKABLE
456 UNIT_FLAG_IMMUNE_TO_PC = 0x00000100, // disables combat/assistance with PlayerCharacters (PC) - see Unit::_IsValidAttackTarget, Unit::_IsValidAssistTarget
457 UNIT_FLAG_IMMUNE_TO_NPC = 0x00000200, // disables combat/assistance with NonPlayerCharacters (NPC) - see Unit::_IsValidAttackTarget, Unit::_IsValidAssistTarget
458 UNIT_FLAG_LOOTING = 0x00000400, // loot animation
459 UNIT_FLAG_PET_IN_COMBAT = 0x00000800, // in combat?, 2.0.8
460 UNIT_FLAG_PVP = 0x00001000, // changed in 3.0.3
461 UNIT_FLAG_SILENCED = 0x00002000, // silenced, 2.1.1
462 UNIT_FLAG_CANNOT_SWIM = 0x00004000, // 2.0.8
463 UNIT_FLAG_SWIMMING = 0x00008000, // shows swim animation in water
464 UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE_2 = 0x00010000, // removes attackable icon, if on yourself, cannot assist self but can cast TARGET_SELF spells - added by SPELL_AURA_MOD_UNATTACKABLE
465 UNIT_FLAG_PACIFIED = 0x00020000, // 3.0.3 ok
466 UNIT_FLAG_STUNNED = 0x00040000, // 3.0.3 ok
467 UNIT_FLAG_IN_COMBAT = 0x00080000,
468 UNIT_FLAG_TAXI_FLIGHT = 0x00100000, // disable casting at client side spell not allowed by taxi flight (mounted?), probably used with 0x4 flag
469 UNIT_FLAG_DISARMED = 0x00200000, // 3.0.3, disable melee spells casting..., "Required melee weapon" added to melee spells tooltip.
470 UNIT_FLAG_CONFUSED = 0x00400000,
471 UNIT_FLAG_FLEEING = 0x00800000,
472 UNIT_FLAG_POSSESSED = 0x01000000, // under direct client control by a player (possess or vehicle)
473 UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE = 0x02000000,
474 UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE = 0x04000000,
475 UNIT_FLAG_MOUNT = 0x08000000,
476 UNIT_FLAG_UNK_28 = 0x10000000,
477 UNIT_FLAG_PREVENT_EMOTES_FROM_CHAT_TEXT = 0x20000000, // Prevent automatically playing emotes from parsing chat text, for example "lol" in /say, ending message with ? or !, or using /yell
478 UNIT_FLAG_SHEATHE = 0x40000000,
479 UNIT_FLAG_IMMUNE = 0x80000000, // Immune to damage
480};

513enum NPCFlags : uint32
514{

517 UNIT_NPC_FLAG_QUESTGIVER = 0x00000002, // TITLE is quest giver DESCRIPTION guessed, probably ok
518 UNIT_NPC_FLAG_UNK1 = 0x00000004,
519 UNIT_NPC_FLAG_UNK2 = 0x00000008,
520 UNIT_NPC_FLAG_TRAINER = 0x00000010, // TITLE is trainer DESCRIPTION 100%
521 UNIT_NPC_FLAG_TRAINER_CLASS = 0x00000020, // TITLE is class trainer DESCRIPTION 100%
522 UNIT_NPC_FLAG_TRAINER_PROFESSION = 0x00000040, // TITLE is profession trainer DESCRIPTION 100%

803class HealInfo
804{
805private:
806 Unit* const m_healer;
807 Unit* const m_target;
808 uint32 m_heal;
809 uint32 m_absorb;
810 SpellInfo const* const m_spellInfo;
811 SpellSchoolMask const m_schoolMask;
812public:
813 explicit HealInfo(Unit* _healer, Unit* _target, uint32 _heal, SpellInfo const* _spellInfo, SpellSchoolMask _schoolMask)
814 : m_healer(_healer), m_target(_target), m_heal(_heal), m_spellInfo(_spellInfo), m_schoolMask(_schoolMask)
815 {
816 m_absorb = 0;
817 }
818 void AbsorbHeal(uint32 amount)
819 {
820 amount = std::min(amount, GetHeal());
821 m_absorb += amount;
822 m_heal -= amount;
823 }
824
825 void SetHeal(uint32 amount)
826 {
827 m_heal = amount;
828 }
829
830 [[nodiscard]] Unit* GetHealer() const { return m_healer; }
831 [[nodiscard]] Unit* GetTarget() const { return m_target; }
832 [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetHeal() const { return m_heal; }
833 [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetAbsorb() const { return m_absorb; }
834 [[nodiscard]] SpellInfo const* GetSpellInfo() const { return m_spellInfo; };
835 [[nodiscard]] SpellSchoolMask GetSchoolMask() const { return m_schoolMask; };
836};

1011enum ActiveStates : uint8
1012{
1013 ACT_PASSIVE = 0x01, // 0x01 - passive

1015 ACT_ENABLED = 0xC1, // 0x40 | 0x80 - auto cast + castable

1035
1036#define UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(X) (uint32(X) & 0x00FFFFFF)
1037#define UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_TYPE(X) ((uint32(X) & 0xFF000000) >> 24)
1038#define MAKE_UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON(A, T) (uint32(A) | (uint32(T) << 24))
1039
1040struct UnitActionBarEntry
1041{
1042 UnitActionBarEntry() : packedData(uint32(ACT_DISABLED) << 24) {}
1043
1044 uint32 packedData;
1045
1046 // helper
1047 [[nodiscard]] ActiveStates GetType() const { return ActiveStates(UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_TYPE(packedData)); }
1048 [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetAction() const { return UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(packedData); }
1049 [[nodiscard]] bool IsActionBarForSpell() const
1050 {
1051 ActiveStates Type = GetType();
1052 return Type == ACT_DISABLED || Type == ACT_ENABLED || Type == ACT_PASSIVE;
1053 }
1054
1055 void SetActionAndType(uint32 action, ActiveStates type)
1056 {
1057 packedData = MAKE_UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON(action, type);
1058 }
1059
1060 void SetType(ActiveStates type)
1061 {
1062 packedData = MAKE_UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON(UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(packedData), type);
1063 }
1064
1065 void SetAction(uint32 action)
1066 {
1067 packedData = (packedData & 0xFF000000) | UNIT_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(action);
1068 }
1069};

1243// pussywizard:
1244class MMapTargetData
1245{
1246public:
1247 MMapTargetData() = default;
1248 MMapTargetData(uint32 endTime, const Position* o, const Position* t)
1249 {
1250 _endTime = endTime;
1251 _posOwner.Relocate(o);
1252 _posTarget.Relocate(t);
1253 }
1254 MMapTargetData(const MMapTargetData& c)
1255 {
1256 _endTime = c._endTime;
1257 _posOwner.Relocate(c._posOwner);
1258 _posTarget.Relocate(c._posTarget);
1259 }
1260 MMapTargetData(MMapTargetData&&) = default;
1261 MMapTargetData& operator=(const MMapTargetData&) = default;
1262 MMapTargetData& operator=(MMapTargetData&&) = default;
1263 [[nodiscard]] bool PosChanged(const Position& o, const Position& t) const
1264 {
1265 return _posOwner.GetExactDistSq(&o) > 0.5f * 0.5f || _posTarget.GetExactDistSq(&t) > 0.5f * 0.5f;
1266 }
1267 uint32 _endTime;
1268 Position _posOwner;
1269 Position _posTarget;
1270};

1273{

1275 explicit SafeUnitPointer(Unit* defVal) : ptr(defVal), defaultValue(defVal) {}
1276 SafeUnitPointer(const SafeUnitPointer& /*p*/) { ABORT(); }
1277 void Initialize(Unit* defVal) { defaultValue = defVal; ptr = defVal; }

1280 void UnitDeleted();
1281 Unit* operator->() const { return ptr; }
1282 void operator=(Unit* u) { SetPointedTo(u); }
1283 operator Unit* () const { return ptr; }
1284private:
1285 Unit* ptr;
1286 Unit* defaultValue;
1287};

1604 [[nodiscard]] bool CanUseAttackType(uint8 attacktype) const
1605 {
1606 switch (attacktype)
1607 {
1608 case BASE_ATTACK:
1609 return !HasUnitFlag(UNIT_FLAG_DISARMED);
1610 case OFF_ATTACK:
1611 return !HasUnitFlag2(UNIT_FLAG2_DISARM_OFFHAND);
1612 case RANGED_ATTACK:
1613 return !HasUnitFlag2(UNIT_FLAG2_DISARM_RANGED);
1614 }
1615 return true;
1616 }
1617
1618 [[nodiscard]] virtual uint32 GetShieldBlockValue() const = 0;
1619 [[nodiscard]] uint32 GetShieldBlockValue(uint32 soft_cap, uint32 hard_cap) const
1620 {
1621 uint32 value = GetShieldBlockValue();
1622 if (value >= hard_cap)
1623 {
1624 value = (soft_cap + hard_cap) / 2;
1625 }
1626 else if (value > soft_cap)
1627 {
1628 value = soft_cap + ((value - soft_cap) / 2);
1629 }
1630
1631 return value;
1632 }

2022 [[nodiscard]] float GetResistanceBuffMods(SpellSchools school, bool positive) const { return GetFloatValue(positive ? static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_RESISTANCEBUFFMODSPOSITIVE) + school : static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_RESISTANCEBUFFMODSNEGATIVE) + + school); }
2023 void SetResistanceBuffMods(SpellSchools school, bool positive, float val) { SetFloatValue(positive ? static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_RESISTANCEBUFFMODSPOSITIVE) + school : static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_RESISTANCEBUFFMODSNEGATIVE) + + school, val); }
2024 void ApplyResistanceBuffModsMod(SpellSchools school, bool positive, float val, bool apply) { ApplyModSignedFloatValue(positive ? static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_RESISTANCEBUFFMODSPOSITIVE) + school : static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_RESISTANCEBUFFMODSNEGATIVE) + + school, val, apply); }
2025 void ApplyResistanceBuffModsPercentMod(SpellSchools school, bool positive, float val, bool apply) { ApplyPercentModFloatValue(positive ? static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_RESISTANCEBUFFMODSPOSITIVE) + school : static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_RESISTANCEBUFFMODSNEGATIVE) + + school, val, apply); }
2026 void InitStatBuffMods()
2027 {
2028 for (uint8 i = STAT_STRENGTH; i < MAX_STATS; ++i) SetFloatValue(static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_POSSTAT0) + i, 0);
2029 for (uint8 i = STAT_STRENGTH; i < MAX_STATS; ++i) SetFloatValue(static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_NEGSTAT0) + i, 0);
2030 }
2031 void ApplyStatBuffMod(Stats stat, float val, bool apply) { ApplyModSignedFloatValue((val > 0 ? static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_POSSTAT0) + stat : static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_NEGSTAT0) + stat), val, apply); }
2032 void ApplyStatPercentBuffMod(Stats stat, float val, bool apply);

2596 // Binary predicate for sorting Units based on percent value of a power
2597 class PowerPctOrderPred
2598 {
2599 public:
2600 PowerPctOrderPred(Powers power, bool ascending = true) : _power(power), _ascending(ascending) { }
2601
2602 bool operator()(WorldObject const* objA, WorldObject const* objB) const
2603 {
2604 Unit const* a = objA->ToUnit();
2605 Unit const* b = objB->ToUnit();
2606 float rA = (a && a->GetMaxPower(_power)) ? float(a->GetPower(_power)) / float(a->GetMaxPower(_power)) : 0.0f;
2607 float rB = (b && b->GetMaxPower(_power)) ? float(b->GetPower(_power)) / float(b->GetMaxPower(_power)) : 0.0f;
2608 return _ascending ? rA < rB : rA > rB;
2609 }
2610
2611 bool operator()(Unit const* a, Unit const* b) const
2612 {
2613 float rA = a->GetMaxPower(_power) ? float(a->GetPower(_power)) / float(a->GetMaxPower(_power)) : 0.0f;
2614 float rB = b->GetMaxPower(_power) ? float(b->GetPower(_power)) / float(b->GetMaxPower(_power)) : 0.0f;
2615 return _ascending ? rA < rB : rA > rB;
2616 }
2617
2618 private:
2619 Powers const _power;
2620 bool const _ascending;
2621 };
2622
2623 // Binary predicate for sorting Units based on percent value of health
2624 class HealthPctOrderPred
2625 {
2626 public:
2627 HealthPctOrderPred(bool ascending = true) : _ascending(ascending) { }
2628
2629 bool operator()(WorldObject const* objA, WorldObject const* objB) const
2630 {
2631 Unit const* a = objA->ToUnit();
2632 Unit const* b = objB->ToUnit();
2633 float rA = (a && a->GetMaxHealth()) ? float(a->GetHealth()) / float(a->GetMaxHealth()) : 0.0f;
2634 float rB = (b && b->GetMaxHealth()) ? float(b->GetHealth()) / float(b->GetMaxHealth()) : 0.0f;
2635 return _ascending ? rA < rB : rA > rB;
2636 }
2637
2638 bool operator() (Unit const* a, Unit const* b) const
2639 {
2640 float rA = a->GetMaxHealth() ? float(a->GetHealth()) / float(a->GetMaxHealth()) : 0.0f;
2641 float rB = b->GetMaxHealth() ? float(b->GetHealth()) / float(b->GetMaxHealth()) : 0.0f;
2642 return _ascending ? rA < rB : rA > rB;
2643 }
2644
2645 private:
2646 bool const _ascending;
2647 };
